      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.225-2</ph> Buy American Certificate.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="provision">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3400e8">As prescribed
in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF">
               <xref href="25.1101.dita#FAR_25_1101"
                     base="i1090819"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">25.1101</xref>(a)(2)</ph>, insert
the following provision:</p>
         <p id="d3401e15"
            outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps"
            rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022-008?>Buy
            American Certificate (Oct
            2022)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.225-2 by—   a. Revising the date of the provision;?></p>
         <ol id="d3361e25">
            <li props="Runin">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3400e19">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3401e26">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2021-008?>The Offeror certifies that
                           each end product, except those listed in paragraph (b) of this provision,
                           is a domestic end product and that each domestic end product listed in
                           paragraph (c) of this provision contains a critical
                           component.<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Revising paragraph (a)(1);?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3401e34">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The Offeror shall list
                        as foreign end products those end products manufactured in the United States
                        that do not qualify as domestic end products. <ph rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2021-008?>For those foreign end
                           products that do not consist wholly or predominantly of iron or steel or
                           a combination of both, the Offeror shall also indicate whether these
                           foreign end products exceed 55 percent domestic content, except for those
                           that are COTS items. If the percentage of the domestic content is
                           unknown, select
                           “no”.<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Adding two sentences at the end of paragraph (a)(2);?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3401e43">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2021-008?>The Offeror shall separately
                           list the line item numbers of domestic end products that contain a
                           critical component (see FAR
                           25.105).<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Redesignating paragraph (a)(3) as paragraph (a)(4) and adding a new paragraph (a)(3); in its place;?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3401e51">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d3401e52">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                           <ph rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2021-008?>Foreign End
                              Products:<?FM MARKER [Why] Start Typingf. Revising the table in paragraph (b);?></ph>
                        </p>
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-05 October 25, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2021-008?>The terms “commercially
                           available off-the-shelf (COTS) item,” “critical
                           component,”<?FM MARKER [Why] e. In newly redesignated paragraph (a)(4) removing the phrase “The terms” and adding the phrase “The terms “commercially available off-the-shelf (COTS) item,” “critical component,” ” in its place;?></ph>
                        "domestic end product," "end product," and "foreign end product" are defined
                        in the clause of this solicitation entitled "Buy American-Supplies."</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
